  "body": "https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/6d97f0919547df11be9443b54af2d90631eaa733/contracts/governance/TimelockController.sol#L346\r\n\r\nI think since there's a lower limit, there should also be a higher limit of delay allowed in governance seeing that updateDelay isn't public or internally overridable to prevent such delays to be validated.\r\n\r\nAlmost all governance controllers have a max delay to avoid queuing up execution for eternity, especially when such votes doesn't make any sense anymore...\r\n\r\nCan i make such feature-request to avoid linking the file directly from my project folder?\r\n\r\nThanks",
