    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "Hello @noobshow \r\n\r\nI max delay is an additional feature, which some people might need while other don't. We try to be unopinionated, and not to had features that are not essentials and can easily be added on top of our contract.\r\n\r\nIf you need such a feature, I believe you should write you own \r\n\r\n```\r\nTimelockControllerWithMaxDelay is TimelockController {\r\n    uint256 private _maxDelay;\r\n    \r\n    constructor(\r\n        uint256 minDelay,\r\n        uint256 maxDelay,\r\n        address[] memory proposers,\r\n        address[] memory executors\r\n    ) TimelockController(minDelay, proposers, executors) {\r\n        _maxDelay = maxDelay;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    function schedule(\r\n        address target,\r\n        uint256 value,\r\n        bytes calldata data,\r\n        bytes32 predecessor,\r\n        bytes32 salt,\r\n        uint256 delay\r\n    ) public virtual override {\r\n        require(delay <= _maxDelay);\r\n        super.schedule(target, value, data, predecessor, salt, delay);\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    function scheduleBatch(\r\n        address[] calldata targets,\r\n        uint256[] calldata values,\r\n        bytes[] calldata datas,\r\n        bytes32 predecessor,\r\n        bytes32 salt,\r\n        uint256 delay\r\n    ) public virtual override {\r\n        require(delay <= _maxDelay);\r\n        super.scheduleBatch(targets, values, datas, predecessor, salt, delay);\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```",
