    "body": "Hi @Amxx,\r\nI believe you got my intentions wrong, i wasn't referring to the `schedule()` delay, i was referring to the delay set here :\r\n```solidity\r\n\tfunction updateDelay(uint256 newDelay) external virtual {\r\n\t\trequire(\r\n\t\t\tmsg.sender == address(this),\r\n\t\t\t\"TimelockController: caller must be timelock\"\r\n\t\t);\r\n\t\trequire(\r\n\t\t\tnewDelay >= _minDelay,\r\n\t\t\t\"TimelockController::setDelay: delay must exceed minimum delay.\"\r\n\t\t);\r\n\t\trequire(\r\n\t\t\tnewDelay <= _maxDelay,\r\n\t\t\t\"TimelockController::setDelay: delay must not exceed maximum delay.\"\r\n\t\t);\r\n\t\temit MinDelayChange(_minDelay, newDelay);\r\n\t\t_minDelay = newDelay;\r\n\t}\r\n```\r\nsuch that the delay won't be set too lax or too short...",
