    "body": "No what I said is definitely possible, I suggested to ignore the `_minDelay` variable and override `getMinDelay` to use a different variable that you declare in a child contract.\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\nimport \"@openzeppelin/contracts/governance/TimelockController.sol\";\r\n\r\ncontract TC is TimelockController {\r\n    constructor(\r\n        uint256 minDelay,\r\n        address[] memory proposers,\r\n        address[] memory executors\r\n    ) TimelockController(minDelay, proposers, executors) {\r\n        _minDelay = minDelay;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    uint _minDelay;\r\n    \r\n    function getMinDelay() public view override returns (uint) {\r\n        return _minDelay;\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    function updateDelay(uint newDelay) external override {\r\n        require(msg.sender == address(this));\r\n        emit MinDelayChange(_minDelay, newDelay);\r\n        _minDelay = newDelay;\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```",
